The paper deals with approximation algorithms for Unique Games, which is a well-studied problem in theoretical computer science. The use of low diameter graph decomposition is a key technique in the paper, which suggests that the paper could belong to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also mentions the constraint graph being of genus g, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper deals with approximation ratios, which suggests that it could belong to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) or cs.IT (Information Theory).
